description: Gets a list of the flywheels that you have created.

parameters.name: Filter
parameters.description: Filters the flywheels that are returned. You can filter flywheels on their status, or the date and time that they were submitted. You can only set one filter at a time. Status (string) --- Filter the flywheels based on the flywheel status. CreationTimeAfter (datetime) --- Filter the flywheels to include flywheels created after the specified time. CreationTimeBefore (datetime) --- Filter the flywheels to include flywheels created before the specified time.

nested_params.name: Status
nested_params.description: Filter the flywheels based on the flywheel status.

nested_params.name: CreationTimeAfter
nested_params.description: Filter the flywheels to include flywheels created after the specified time.

nested_params.name: CreationTimeBefore
nested_params.description: Filter the flywheels to include flywheels created before the specified time.

nested_items.name: FlywheelSummaryList
nested_items.description: A list of flywheel properties retrieved by the service in response to the request.

nested_items.name: FlywheelArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Number (ARN) of the flywheel.

nested_items.name: ActiveModelArn
nested_items.description: ARN of the active model version for the flywheel.

nested_items.name: DataLakeS3Uri
nested_items.description: Amazon S3 URI of the data lake location.

nested_items.name: ModelType
nested_items.description: Model type of the flywheel's model.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: A description of the status of the flywheel.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: Last modified time for the flywheel.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: Identifies the next page of results to return.
